Subject: drm/amdgpu: limit the VM address space with older VCE FW versions
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit
Git-commit: 6b034e25c86805d14259668a3ce6dc27c7509557
Patch-mainline: v4.17-rc1
References: FATE#326289 FATE#326079 FATE#326049 FATE#322398 FATE#326166

Older VCE FW versions are buggy and can't work with 48bit address
spaces.

RFC: Should we limit the address space or just reject loading the older
VCE firmware?

